ne Oxenberg]]\n|9 days\n|July 12\u201321, 1998\n|Evans's fifth of seven marriages. Annulled.\n|<ref name=evansobit>[https://www.voanews.com/arts-culture/robert-evans-iconic-producer-chinatown-dies-89 Robert Evans, Iconic Producer of 'Chinatown,' Dies at 89]</ref>\n|-\n|[[Pamela Anderson]] and [[Jon Peters]]\n|12 days\n|January 20\u2013February 1, 2020\n|Marriage certificate never officially enacted.\n|<ref>https://www.msn.com/en-us/tv/celebrity/pamela-anderson-and-movie-mogul-jon-peters-call-it-quits/ar-BBZywW2?ocid=spartandhp</ref>\n|-\n|[[Patty Duke]] and Michael Tell\n|13 days\n|June 26 \u2013 July 9, 1970\n|Annulled. Marriage produced a child, [[Sean Astin]], whom Duke mistakenly believed to be fathered by [[Desi Arnaz, Jr.]] at the time.\n|<ref>{{cite web|last=Lipton |first=Michael A. |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20128097,00.html |title=People Magazine on Patty Duke |publisher=People.com |date=1999-05-03 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Victoria Barrett |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2003/dec/19/lordoftherings.features |title=The Guardian on Sean Astin |publisher=Guardian |date= 2003-12-19|accessdate=2011-02-21 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reviewjournal.com/lvrj_home/2004/Feb-29-Sun-2004/news/23327549.html |title=2004 Article on Michael Tell from Las Vegas Review-Journal |publisher=Reviewjournal.com |date=2004-02-29 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Eddie Murphy]] and [[Tracey Edmonds]]\n|2 weeks\n|January 2008\n|\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Mario Lopez]] and [[Ali Landry]]\n|18 days\n|April 24 \u2013 May 2004\n|\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2098279_2098285_2098287,00.html|title=Top 10 Short-Lived Celebrity Marriages|first=Terri|last=Pous|date=November 1, 2011|via=content.time.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Drew Barrymore]] and Jeremy Thomas\n|19 days\n|February\u2014March 1994\n|\n|<ref name=\"usatoday2005\">{{cite news|author=Karen Thomas, USA TODAY |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2005-09-15-zellweger-chesney_x.htm |title=USA Today |publisher=USA Today |date=2005-09-16 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Ernest Borgnine]] and [[Ethel Merman]]\n|42 days\n|June 27 \u2013 August 4, 1964\n|Separated August 4, divorce mutually requested October 21 and granted November 18.\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2512&dat=19641022&id=50BIAAAAIBAJ&sjid=CwENAAAAIBAJ&pg=2166,5885684|title=Borgnine Sues Merman For Divorce|date=October 22, 1964|work=The Morning Record|page=20|accessdate=September 20, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kim Darby]] and James Westmoreland\n|47 days\n|1970\n|\n|<ref name=\"The Prescott Courier \u2013 Google News Archive Search\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=IKhMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=alADAAAAIBAJ&pg=2321,4088324&dq=|title=The Prescott Courier \u2013 Google News Archive Search|website=news.google.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Ethel Merman]] and William Smith\n|2 months\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Milla Jovovich]] and [[Shawn Andrews (actor)|Shawn Andrews]]\n|2 months\n|1992\n|Annulled.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/resident-evil-star-milla-jovovich-admits-she-married-shawn-andrews-as-a-teenager-as-she-wanted-a-bank-card/news-story/03970a5f26e35d31eb9cdda6cc324f43|title=Married for a bank card|date=July 11, 2011|website=www.dailytelegraph.com.au}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Chris Kattan]] and Sunshine Deia Tutt\n|2 months\n|\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nj.com/entertainment/celebrities/2008/09/kattan_and_tutt.html|title=Chris Kattan's estranged wife may clean up in divorce|first=Vicki|last=Hyman|date=September 26, 2008|website=nj.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kim Kardashian]] and [[Kris Humphries]]\n|72 days\n|2011\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/news/a348420/kim-kardashian-filing-for-divorce-from-kris-humphries-today.html|title=Kim Kardashian files for divorce}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://us99country.radio.com/2011/10/31/apparently-the-kim-kardashian-and-kris-humphries-marriage-is-over/|title=WUSN-FM/US99.5|access-date=2013-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309131310/http://us99country.radio.com/2011/10/31/apparently-the-kim-kardashian-and-kris-humphries-marriage-is-over/|archive-date=2012-03-09|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kid Rock]] and [[Pamela Anderson]]\n|121 days\n|July 29 \u2013 November 27, 2006\n|\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Nicolas Cage]] and [[Lisa Marie Presley]]\n|108 days\n|2002\n|Divorce took over a year to be finalized.\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://breakingnews.iol.ie/entertainment/?jp=kfeysnmhojoj |title=IOL |publisher=Breakingnews.iol.ie |date=2004-05-26 |accessdate=2011-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308050052/http://breakingnews.iol.ie/entertainment/?jp=kfeysnmhojoj |archive-date=2012-03-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/popculture/cage-presley-divorce-made-final-wbna5061500 |title=MSNBC |publisher=Today.com |date=2004-05-25 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref><ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Colin Farrell]] and [[Amelia Warner]]\n|> 4 months\n|July 17\u2014November, 2001\n|\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Bradley Cooper]] and [[Jennifer Esposito]]\n|4 months\n|\n|\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Ren\u00e9e Zellweger]] and [[Kenny Chesney]]\n|4 months\n|May 2005\u20142005\n|Annulled.\n|<ref name=\"usatoday2005\" />\n|-\n|[[Sophia Bush]] and [[Chad Michael Murray]]\n|5 months\n|April\u2014September 2005\n|Separated (September 2005). Bush unsuccessfully petitioned for annulment (February 2006). Divorced (December 2006).\n|<ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Charlie Sheen]] and Donna Peele\n|5 months\n|September 1995 \u2013 1996\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2011/01/29/porn-star-tells-of-coke-and-booze-orgy-with-charlie-sheen-before-hospital-dash-115875-22882934/ |title=The Mirror |publisher=The Mirror |date=2011-01-29 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Cl1OAAAAIBAJ&sjid=9_wDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4869,6687172&dq=charlie-sheen+donna&hl=en |title=Lakeland Ledger \u2013 February 20, 1996 |date=1996-02-20 |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref><ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Irving Berlin]] and Dorothy Goetz\n|5 months\n|February 1912 \u2014 July 17, 1912\n|Unlike most listed here, the end of the marriage was caused by Goetz contracting [[typhoid fever]] on their Cuban honeymoon and dying. Berlin's second marriage would last 62 years.\n|-\n|[[Drew Barrymore]] and [[Tom Green]]\n|163 days\n|July 7 \u2013 December 17, 2001\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web |last=Silverman |first=Stephen M. |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,622131,00.html |title=(magazine) |publisher=People |date=2001-07-10 |accessdate=2011-02-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080605161742/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,622131,00.html |archivedate=2008-06-05 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Darst |first=Jeanne |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,623114,00.html |title=(magazine) |publisher=People |date=2001-12-18 |accessdate=2011-02-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005070527/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,623114,00.html |archivedate=2008-10-05 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"nineteen\" />\n|-\n|[[Shannen Doherty]] and [[Ashley Hamilton]]\n|> 6 months\n|1993 \u2013 March 1994\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=GcIdAAAAIBAJ&sjid=1r4EAAAAIBAJ&pg=6891,4601899&dq=ashley+hamilton&hl=en |title=Sarasota Herald-Tribune \u2013 April 8, 1994 |date= |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=CHMaAAAAIBAJ&sjid=zCwEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5321,6847621&dq=ashley+hamilton&hl=en |title=The Milwaukee Journal \u2013 April 7, 1994 |date= |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kim Darby]] and [[James Stacy]]\n|7 months\n|\n|\n|<r