]]'' #119. Retrieved 2008-01-17.</ref><ref name=Skinflicks>[https://books.google.com/books?id=3VCVm7sc5JsC&pg=PA291&lpg=PA291&dq=%22Rachel+Ryan%22+Keaton&source=web&ots=08f9A-XpH7&sig=KaZLA-NyPIynarenCUhhEDdiQYg#PPA290,M1 ''Skinflicks: The Inside Story of the X-Rated Video Industry''], by David Jennings, 2000, AuthorHouse, {{ISBN|1-58721-184-X}}, pages 290\u2013291. [[Google Books]] page retrieved 2008-01-17.</ref>\n|}\n\n== Entertainers married 50 years or more ==\nEntertainment couples that last for decades, and/or life, are occasionally used as a counterpoint when referring to \"Hollywood marriage\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=v9wqAAAAIBAJ&sjid=GkoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=2969,2107034&dq=hollywood-marriage&hl=en |title=\"A Hollywood Marriage That Succeeded\", article on Ida Cantor's death from The Deseret News on August 10, 1962 |date= |accessdate=2011-02-21}}</ref> In relation to that, here is a selection of entertainers who have or had marriages that lasted over 50 years.\n\n(Note that in a few of these cases, the entertainers were not necessarily in ''faithful'' marriages. Tom Jones, for example, was widely known to effectively be in an [[open relationship]] and had many extramarital affairs throughout his marriage.)\n\nLegend:<br />\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Living couples, still married|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Names\n! Length\n! Marriage\n! Source\n|-\n|[[Irving Benson]] and Lillian Waldowsky\n|79 years, 105 days\n|November 19, 1936 \u2013 March 3, 2016 (her death)\n|<ref>{{cite news|last=Starr|first=Michael|title=Johnny Carson's favorite comic still standing|url=https://nypost.com/2014/01/15/johnny-carsons-favorite-comic-still-standing/|publisher=New York York Post|accessdate=16 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Norman Lloyd]] and [[Peggy Lloyd]]\n|75 years, 65 days\n|June 26, 1936 \u2013 August 30, 2011 (her death)\n|<ref name=variety>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Broadway thesp Peggy Lloyd dies at 98